	<!-- custom: rename "Ivory" to "Elephants", there are 2 main reasons
	for why i suggest this change i mean anyways: 
	- 1) you need elephants to build war elephants, not ivory, even if you
	were to somehow find ivory somewhere, it would/could not magically turn
	into a war elephant, so using the animal instead i mean anyways makes much
	more sense i think -why no one thought ofor did this rather maybe? I mean
	 anwyays
	- 2) ivory doesn't grow on the groud, if i am not mistaken and understand
	it correctly i mean anwyays, but is derived from elephants, whether they
	are alive or dead (could be traded though but it's about terrain ressources
	in this case i mean anyways). So it is more immersive, realistic, and making
	sense to use "Elephants" instead of ivory i think i mean anyways. One could
	also maybe imagine that elephants the animal itself makes people happy, like
	for the zoo or something?
	note: Since they are part of the animals that are countable in english rather
	than uncountable (see discussion (actually link and my code comments i mean
	anyways..) below about cattle if i am not mistaken) and seeing that civ4
	doesn't seem to bother with singulars too much about animals at least i mean
	anyways, (and i like it	better this way and/or also thinks itsmore fit to this
